JUST USE THIS INSTEAD TO BE SAFE:

x - delete a letter

X - delete a letter before the cursor

dw - delete a word

dW - delete a word including the punctuation mark

dd - delete the entire line no matter where your cursor is

2dd - delete 2 entier lines


NOTE:

d - the delete operator

you can use this plus the motion you want to delete.

Ex:

dw - delete word

dk - delete line upward

dj - delete line downward

d0 - delete line from cursor to the beginning of the line

d$ - delete line from cursor to the end of the line - shortcut is D



you can also do the operator[count]{motion}

Ex: d5w - delete 5 words from the cursor
